# One Acre

The Dream to Work a One Acre Farm for a Day (or Farm Game for a lifetime!)

Can I convince my daughter that tile games are anywhere near as fun as
Roblox?!

Inspired by an epside of Lost when Desmond mentions the{" "}

<Link url="https://lostpedia.fandom.com/wiki/Snowglobe">Snowglobe</Link> and Brad
hypes <Link url="https://mythic-quest.fandom.com/wiki/Battle_Royale_mode">
  Battle Royale Mode
</Link> on Mythic Quest, I wanted to build a small, diorama-type experiment which
features an Area of Affect where a circle will the affect tiles hilighting those
within the circle and darkening those beyond.

As the cirlce shrinks, the agents will need to move closer to the center and
come in closer contact. Each agent will be able to cast an AOE spell that
could push (a nod to <Link url="https://www.polygon.com/2018/2/26/17053646/into-the-breach-preview-impressions-difficulty-ftl-roguelike-pc">
Into the Breach</Link>) the other agent outside of the circle and perish.

the quest to produce energy instead of consuming it. How can we tip the scales?!

