### Data Trees & Directed Graphs

When harvesting D3 scripts from

<Link url="https://bl.ocks.org/">Bl.ocks</Link>

<Link url="https://observablehq.com/">Observerable</Link>, you may discover that
they do a lot in each function. Any time you see long functions, this is an
opportunity to refactor and make it easier to maintain. These long functions are
basically pipelines that assemble the final visualization and their attention
to <Link url="https://d3js.org/d3-scale-chromatic">
  colour and cartography
</Link> drew in me.

Each step in the pipeline can (and should be) its own function. So when you
copy and paste in a long function, take this opportunity to break it up and
learn from each step!

